Your ODF 4.19 bundle images are NOT properly mirrored in disconnected registry.

That is why:

unpack job timed out

CSVs stay Pending

ServiceAccounts are never created

install strategy never executes


Fix it directly.

First identify missing image.

Run:

oc get packagemanifest odf-operator -n openshift-marketplace -o yaml | grep -A5 -i relatedImages

You will see images like:

registry.redhat.io/odf4/...
registry.redhat.io/rhceph/...
quay.io/...

Now mirror ALL missing ODF 4.19 images into harbor.

Example:

oc adm catalog mirror \
nwharbor.sec.samsung.net/team-ocp/ocp/redhat/redhat-operator-index:v4.19 \
nwharbor.sec.samsung.net/team-ocp/ocp/redhat \
-a pull-secret.txt

OR if already mirrored partially, manually mirror missing bundle image:

skopeo copy \
docker://registry.redhat.io/odf4/odf-operator-bundle-rhel9:v4.19.12 \
docker://nwharbor.sec.samsung.net/team-ocp/ocp/redhat/odf4/odf-operator-bundle-rhel9:v4.19.12

Also mirror:

cephcsi

rook

noobaa/mcg

prometheus

recipe

csi addons


After mirroring, restart marketplace + OLM:

oc delete pod -n openshift-marketplace --all

oc delete pod -n openshift-operator-lifecycle-manager --all

Then delete broken pending CSVs again:

oc delete csv \
cephcsi-operator.v4.18.17-rhodf \
mcg-operator.v4.18.17-rhodf \
ocs-client-operator.v4.18.17-rhodf \
ocs-operator.v4.18.17-rhodf \
odf-csi-addons-operator.v4.18.17-rhodf \
odf-prometheus-operator.v4.18.17-rhodf \
recipe.v4.18.17-rhodf \
odf-dependencies.v4.18.17-rhodf \
-n openshift-storage

Then force reconcile:

oc annotate sub odf-operator \
-n openshift-storage \
force-reconcile="$(date +%s)" --overwrite

Then monitor:

watch 'oc get csv,pods -n openshift-storage'

This time:

unpack succeeds

installplan created

ServiceAccounts created

Deployments created

CSVs become Succeeded.
